# Full API Checkup: `/profile/circles/${circleId}/location`

I have performed a codebase-wide checkup of all occurrences of the circle location update API.

## Summary of Findings

The API is strictly invoked in **two specific locations** within the codebase, both of which are now standardized to a **30-second frequency**.

| File | Context | Frequency | Trigger |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [app/screens/MapScreen.tsx](file:///d:/360app/app/screens/MapScreen.tsx) | Foreground Tracking | Fixed 30s | `Location.watchPositionAsync` |
| [services/BackgroundLocationService.ts](file:///d:/360app/services/BackgroundLocationService.ts) | Background Service | Fixed 30s | `BackgroundService` (Android) / `TaskManager` (iOS) |

---

## Detailed Call Checkup

### 1. [app/screens/MapScreen.tsx](file:///d:/360app/app/screens/MapScreen.tsx)
- **Function:** [maybePostCircleLocationUpdate](file:///d:/360app/app/screens/MapScreen.tsx#556-608)
- **Call Frequency:** strictly every **30 seconds**.
- **Conditions for call:**
    - Must have an active `circleId` selected.
    - `user_location_sharing_enabled` must be `true` in `AsyncStorage`.
    - Geographic coordinates must be valid finite numbers.
- **Recent Standardizations:**
    - Removed **20-meter distance filter** (previously skipped updates if the user didn't move).
    - Removed **Journey Logic** (previously caused bursts or status updates after 5-minute gaps).

### 2. [services/BackgroundLocationService.ts](file:///d:/360app/services/BackgroundLocationService.ts)
- **Function:** [syncLocationQueue](file:///d:/360app/services/BackgroundLocationService.ts#49-104) (called via [backgroundTask](file:///d:/360app/services/BackgroundLocationService.ts#117-165) on Android and `TaskManager` on iOS).
- **Call Frequency:** strictly every **30 seconds**.
- **Conditions for call:**
    - Must have a `lastSelectedCircleId` in `AsyncStorage`.
    - **Internet Connectivity:** If offline, locations are queued and synced later via the same API.
    - **Platform Handling:**
        - **Android:** Managed via `react-native-background-actions` with a 30s heartbeat.
        - **iOS:** Managed via `expo-task-manager` with `timeInterval: 30000`.

## Verdict
The codebase is now fully synchronized to a **strict 30-second heartbeat** for location updates. There are no other hidden calls or intermittent triggers for this specific API.
